<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Phase 4E e2e fix (2026-05-07): the helper shares state with
      the parent macOS app via the Group Container at
      ~/Library/Group Containers/group.yyh.CLI-Pulse/ (UDS socket,
      auth token, claude snapshot files). Without
      `application-groups` listing the same group as the parent
      app, the kernel blocks the helper's Data.write / bind() calls
      against that path — process hangs forever in the open()
      syscall. Phase 4D shipped this file empty; the helper has
      been bundled-but-inert since then. Confirmed via
      `sample <pid>` showing AuthToken.rotateToken hung in __open.

      The team-identifier entry MUST match the parent app's team
      so macOS can validate the embedded LaunchAgent's entitlements
      against the parent's provisioning profile. The parent's
      profile already lists the group capability, so the embedded
      helper inherits the right via nested-binary signing.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>group.yyh.CLI-Pulse</string>
    </array>
    <!--
      B3-bis (2026-05-12): added to let the daemon read the
      `helper_secret` keychain entry the macOS app writes during
      pairing (`KeychainHelper.save(..., accessGroup: "group.yyh.CLI-Pulse")`
      in CLIPulseCore). Without this entitlement, `SecItemCopyMatching`
      with `kSecAttrAccessGroup` returns `errSecMissingEntitlement`
      and the daemon falls through to the legacy JSON path even when
      modern UserDefaults pairing is populated — the very bug B3-bis
      fixes.

      `$(AppIdentifierPrefix)` expands at codesign time to the team
      ID prefix (`KHMK6Q3L3K.`), producing the keychain access-group
      string macOS uses internally. The literal `group.yyh.CLI-Pulse`
      (no prefix) is what `AppGroupConfigReader.readPairing()` passes
      at query time — Apple's keychain APIs auto-prepend the prefix.
    -->
    <key>keychain-access-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>$(AppIdentifierPrefix)group.yyh.CLI-Pulse</string>
    </array>
    <key>com.apple.developer.team-identifier</key>
    <string>KHMK6Q3L3K</string>
</dict>
</plist>
